<p>Epithalon (also spelled Epitalon) is a synthetic version of <strong>epithalamin</strong>, a <a href="/articles/what-are-peptides-beginners-guide">peptide</a> naturally produced by the pineal gland. Its full sequence is just four <a href="/articles/what-are-peptides-beginners-guide">amino acids</a> long, making it one of the smallest bioactive peptides in longevity research.</p>

